==English==
{{wikipedia|Sudovian language}}
===Etymology===
From [[Sudovia]].

===Proper adjective===
'''Sudovian'''
# of, relating to, or from [[Sudovia]]
# of or relating to the [[Sudovian]] [[language]]
# {{historical}} of or relating to the Sudovian tribe

===Proper noun===
{{en-proper noun}}
# {{historical}} a member of the [[Prussian]] tribe that inhabited [[Sudovia]].
# a person from [[Sudovia]] or of Sudovian descent.
# the Western Baltic language of the Sudovian people, related to [[Old Prussian]].

===Synonyms===
*[[Jatvingian]]
*[[Yatvingian]], [[Yotvingian]]

